Calgro Climbs to Two-Year High as Earnings Increase

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-07-28T09:17:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/calgro-climbs-to-two-year-high-as-earnings-increase-correct-.html
(Corrects rand to cents in second paragraph.)  Calgro M3 Holdings Ltd. (CGR)  climbed to
the highest in more than two years in Johannesburg after the
company said it expects an improvement of more than 250 percent
in earnings per share for the six months to Aug. 31.  Shares in the company gained as much as 5.9 percent to 90
cents, the highest since May 2009, where the stock was trading
as of 10:47 a.m. local time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at   areed12@bloomberg.net  